Section 6.			CHOICE TIDBITS

				A Healthier You

The following are 10 tips to help you maintain a healthier life.

1. Be realistic with your goals.

2. Examine your eating habits, start planning your meals and avoid eating 
   high-fat snacks.

3. Count the fat grams you eat every day and make sure they account for 
   less than 30 percent of your total calorie consumption.

4. Eat a balanced diet, including foods from every food group.

5. Choose foods high in complex carbohydrates such as fruits, vegetables, 
   pasta and whole grains.

6. Commit to at least 30 minutes of aerobic exercise, such as walking, 
   cycling or dancing, at least five days a week.

7. Schedule exercise appointments just as you would any other important
  appointments.

8. Try low-fat or non-fat snacks, such as frozen yogurt instead of ice cream.

9. Take healthy snacks to work, such as pretzels, fresh fruit or cut-up
  vegetables.

10. Don't give up. If you fall off your schedule, start again the next day.

			(Let's Live, April 1996)

